value.value: A diphenylmethylpiperazine derivative and respiratory stimulant that can be used to improve oxygenation. Upon systemic administration, almitrine targets, binds to and activates the peripheral chemoreceptors located on the carotid bodies. This enhances respiration and increases arterial oxygen tension while decreasing arterial carbon dioxide tension.
A quinolinone sulfooxime and inhibitor of Na-K-Cl cotransporters 1 and 2 with diuretic activity.

label.value: Oral Cavity and Lip Precancerous Condition

value.value: A premalignant pathologic process that affects the mucosa surface of the oral cavity or lip.  It includes leukoplakia, erythroplakia, and smoker's keratosis.
A furosemide derivative belonging to the class of loop diuretics.
A benzenesulfonamide-based agent with salidiuretic and antihypertensive effects.
A furosemide derivative belonging to the class of loop diuretics.
A triazine-based diuretic agent. Amanozine is structurally similar to the diuretic agent chlorazanil.
A sulfamoylchlorobenzoic acid derivative with diuretic activity. Besulpamide appears to be similar in diuretic activity to that of chlorthalidone, clopamide and xipamide.
A hydrazinopyridazine-based diuretic with antihypertensive activity. Hydracarbazine is no longer marketed.
An ethacrynic derivative with diuretic activity.
A sulfanilamide derivative and carbonic anhydrase inhibitor with diuretic activity.
A pyrimidinediamine derivative and dihydrofolate reductase inhibitor related to trimethoprim, with bactericide and diuretic activities. Aditeren has never been marketed.

label.value: Metastatic Malignant Neoplasm in the Rectum

value.value: The spread of a malignant neoplasm to the rectum.  This may be from a primary large intestine malignant neoplasm, or from a malignant neoplasm at a distant site.
